Manus,

I was recently in a game where two of us were discussing the possibility
of a 2-way draw, so I went to the pouch (of course) to find out about
games that end in a 2-way draw. I found very little.
There were some hints in the stalemate articles about stalemate lines
that include 17 SCs, but none of them said whether the other side was
defensible. That was about it.

I think it's an interesting area (particularly "how do you avoid that
final stab"), possibly worthy of an article. I also feel that I'm not
qualified to write it (I didn't manage to find out what I wanted and
settled for a 3-way. I've also never seen a game that ended in a 2-way),
but perhaps one of your more experienced colleagues is ?

Just a suggestion.

-- 
Chris

